          "question": "<p><a name=\"58893\"></a><div itemprop=\"text\">\n<p>Which one of the following is the correct implementation of the meta-predicate “not” in PROLOG (Here G represents a goal)?</p>\n\n\n</div><br><br><b>Artificial Intelligence: UGC NET CSE | June 2013 | Part 3 | Question: 67</b></p>",
          "type": "single",
          "options": [
            "<p>not(G):- !, call(G), fail. not(G).</p>",
            "<p>not(G):- call(G), !, fail. not(G).</p>",
            "<p>not(G):- call(G), fail, !, not(G).</p>",
            "<p>not(G):- call(G), !, fail.not(G):- !.</p>"
          ],
          "correct_answer": "<p>not(G):- call(G), !, fail. not(G).</p>",
